By S. Behera, G. Kumar, M. P. Panigrahi, S. K. Pande, S. Sahoo

This study involved a comprehensive review of various deep learning approaches to forecast solar power generation. Solar power generation is intermittent, but deep learning techniques have proven effective in predicting it. This research contains a detailed review.

data.title: Solar power demand and compensation forecasting
data.description:
• Composed a deep learning-based system to scrutinize solar energy demand, generation, and compensation, tackling the duck-curve effect that leads to an annual energy loss of 15%-20%.

  • Analyzed multiple deep learning models, including LSTM, GRU, DSE-XGB, and BiLSTM, with GRU achieving the best performance based on evaluation metrics (MSE, MAE, MAPE) with a 9.08% error.

  • Integrated both regression and classification models to predict power usage patterns and optimize 5 compensation strategies for fluctuating demand.

  • Optimized the gap between farms and markets by providing ease of sale to local farmers with affordable storage options and market access.

  • Delivered informed analytics to each user to track processes, expenditures and sales.
